The paper deals with the problem of generating interpretable recommendations based on purchase history, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR). The algorithm presented in the paper uses matrix factorization techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the importance of transparency and trust in the recommendation process, which is relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.CE).
